org.numenta.nupic

Class ComputeCycle

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.numenta.nupic.ComputeCycle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Persistable

    public class ComputeCycle
extends java.lang.Object
implements Persistable
    Contains a snapshot of the state attained during one computational call to the TemporalMemory. The TemporalMemory uses data from previous compute cycles to derive new data for the current cycle through a comparison between states of those different cycles, therefore this state container is necessary.
    Author:
    David Ray
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
